examples: We have sufficient supplies to last the winter.
There is not sufficient access to the Internet in many small rural villages.

definitions.definition: A quantity (of something) that is as large as is needed.
examples: We don't need any more; we already have sufficient .
Sufficient of us are against this idea that we should stop now.

secondary_definitions: ( as pronoun ) A quantity (of something) that is as large as is needed.
